description: Margarethe Fellerer (1886-1961), born in Linz, Austria, was a popular portrait photographer. She is most acclaimed for her work in Ascona, Switzerland, where she moved in 1909. Her portraiture focused on the Monte Verità intellectual circle including members of Eranos, who held conferences in the Ascona area. Fellerer was the first official photographer for the Eranos conferences. She was married to artist Ernst Frick.  The bulk of the subseries is portrait photographs by Margarethe Fellerer of artists and intellectuals who were affiliated with the Monte Verità community in Ascona. Szeemann was particularly interested in this portraiture because of his own home in the Ticino canton and also for his 1978 exhibition Monte Verità and its permanent installation at the Museum Casa Anatta. Photographs were indentified by Szeemann as either first or second choice, probably for selections for an exhibition or a publication. His "see also" notes were transcribed from labels when legible. This subseries contains approximately 4,000 negatives and 800 prints. The negatives are predominantly nitrate and are therefore restricted (Box 252-Box 267).
label: Margarethe Fellerer photographs of Monte Verità, Series IV.C.

metadata.value: Files are arranged in Szeemann's original alphabetical order.
